            "query": "How do I force delete a pod that is stuck in the 'Terminating' state?",
            "retrieved_contexts": [
                "\n         ### Force Delete a Terminating Pod\n        To force delete a pod that is stuck in the 'Terminating' state, you can use the following `kubectl` command:\n\n        `kubectl delete pod <pod-name> --force --grace-period=0 -n <namespace>`\n\n        **Explanation:**\n        - `kubectl delete pod <pod-name>`: Specifies the pod to be deleted.\n        - `--force`: Forces the deletion of the resource.\n        - `--grace-period=0`: Sets the grace period to 0 seconds, meaning the pod will be terminated immediately without waiting for a graceful shutdown.\n        - `-n <namespace>`: Specifies the namespace where the pod resides. Replace `<pod-name>` and `<namespace>` with the actual name of your pod and its namespace.\n       "
            ],
            "expected_contexts": [
